					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-572173#post-2513115</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-572173/scp-1766#post-2513115</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 23 May 2016 04:31:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Milo359</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2374168</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The fact that this isn't Keter <strong>really</strong> bugs me. I mean, come on, there's a fake aircraft going around in other aircraft's flight paths which causes them<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-256253-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup> to go into the flight paths of <strong>other</strong> aircrafts and can only be dissipated by a specific frequency of waves, and the Foundation <strong>doesn't</strong> have a grace period to find it and get to it to broadcast the signal, and it's <strong>only</strong> Euclid?</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-256253-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. not directly, I know</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-572173#post-1831288</guid>
